Various roads around Orlando in Soweto have been closed ahead of the official memorial service for fiery struggle heroine Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. The official memorial is expected to begin at Madikizela-Mandela’s Orlando West home and proceed to the Orlando Stadium. Programme for the official State memorial of Mama Winnie Madikizela-Mandela today at the Orlando Stadium from 11am. If you’ll be driving to the venue you are advised to park at Nasrec, there will be no parking at the stadium. pic.twitter.com/73zw5Fbbki — Min. Nathi Mthethwa (@NathiMthethwaSA) April 11, 2018 Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) spokesperson Edna Mamonyane said Mooki Street in Orlando had been closed and the Soweto Motorway up to Sofasonke Street had also been closed. “Klipvalley road from the N17 up to Khumalo, no vehicles will be allowed”,  Mamonyane said. “People attending the memorial are requested to please go and park at Nasrec Expo Centre, there will be buses transporting them to the venue”. Rea Vaya bus routes in Soweto have not been closed, therefore the service is operating as normal. Commuters are made aware that due to the memorial of Mama Winnie Madikizela Mandela at Orlando Stadium, routes will be affected, delays are expected!^CL — Rea Vaya Bus Transit (@ReaVayaBus) April 11, 2018 Rea Vaya bus routes have not been closed therefore the service operating as normal.^CL — Rea Vaya Bus Transit (@ReaVayaBus) April 11, 2018 Hassle free commuting to the memorial service of Mama Winnie Madikizela Mandela, use Rea Vaya to Orlando Stadium.^CL — Rea Vaya Bus Transit (@ReaVayaBus) April 11, 2018 Madikizela-Mandela will be buried on Saturday at a cemetery in Fourways alongside her late granddaughter Zenani. -TNA Reporter